n temp directory for cursor's config\\n2. Pre-seed `<tempDir>/cursor/cli-config.json` with `{}`\\n3. Add `XDG_CONFIG_HOME=<tempDir>` to the env args (cursor follows XDG conventions on Linux)\\n4. Also set `HOME` to a per-test temp dir as fallback (cursor may derive config path from HOME rather than XDG_CONFIG_HOME)\\n5. Register cleanup via `OnClose()` on the TmuxSession\\n\\n**Changes to `startInteractiveSession` signature:** Return `*TmuxSession` + `func()` cleanup (or register cleanup internally via OnClose).\\n\\nSince `startInteractiveSession` returns a `*TmuxSession` which has `OnClose`, we can register the cleanup there. But the caller (RunPrompt, StartSession) already calls `s.Close()`, so the cleanup will run.\\n\\n**Simplify `Bootstrap()`:** Remove the pre-seed logic (lines 83-90) since each session will have its own config dir. Keep the `CURSOR_API_KEY` check and the `MkdirAll` for the shared dir (harmless safety net, but can be removed).\\n\\n### Verification\\n\\n1. `mise run fmt && mise run lint`\\n2. `mise run test:e2e:canary` — must pass (Vogon agent)\\n3. `mise run test:e2e --agent cursor-cli TestDirtyWorkingTree` — the actual failing test\\n\\n\\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/alisha/.claude/projects/-Users-alisha-Projects-devenv-cli/11d7ac69-ed02-4eed-9acd-94e8717b7dfb.jsonl\"},\"uuid\":\"41179dd5-b427-4c93-bd53-1656d24a8407\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-08T22:22:16.640Z\",\"planContent\":\"# Fix: TestDirtyWorkingTree cursor-cli ENOENT race\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nCI run `22809907314` (on commit `3373091e` which already has the pre-seed fix) still failed `TestDirtyWorkingTree` with cursor-cli. The error:\\n\\n```\\nError: ENOENT: no such file or directory, rename '/home/runner/.config/cursor/cli-config.json.tmp' -> '/home/runner/.config/cursor/cli-config.json'\\n```\\n\\n**Root cause:** Pre-seeding `cli-config.json` with `{}` prevents the *initial creation* race, but not the *write-after-trust-acceptance* race. When the workspace trust dialog appears and is accepted, cursor writes the config file atomically (write `.tmp`, rename `.tmp` → target). With 43 parallel tests sharing `~/.config/cursor/`, multiple cursor processes race on the same `.tmp` file.\\n\\n**Classification: flaky (test-bug)** — the CLI works fine; the test infrastructure shares a mutable config directory across parallel cursor sessions.\\n\\n## Fix\\n\\nIsolate the cursor config directory per-session, following the same pattern Claude Code uses with `CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR` / `cleanConfigDir()`.\\n\\n### File: `e2e/agents/cursor_cli.go`\\n\\n**In `startInteractiveSession`:**\\n1. Create a per-session temp directory for cursor's config\\n2. Pre-seed `<tempDir>/cursor/cli-config.json` with `{}`\\n3. Add `XDG_CONFIG_HOME=<tempDir>` to the env args (cursor follows XDG conventions on Linux)\\n4. Also set `HOME` to a per-test temp dir as fallback (cursor may derive config path from HOME rather than XDG_CONFIG_HOME)\\n5. Register cleanup via `OnClose()` on the TmuxSession\\n\\n**Changes to `startInteractiveSession` signature:** Return `*TmuxSession` + `func()` cleanup (or register cleanup internally via OnClose).\\n\\nSince `startInteractiveSession` returns a `*TmuxSession` which has `OnClose`, we can register the cleanup there. But the caller (RunPrompt, StartSession) already calls `s.Close()`, so the cleanup will run.\\n\\n**Simplify `Bootstrap()`:** Remove the pre-seed logic (lines 83-90) since each session will have its own config dir. Keep the `CURSOR_API_KEY` check and the `MkdirAll` for the shared dir (harmless safety net, but can be removed).\\n\\n### Verification\\n\\n1. `mise run fmt && mise run lint`\\n2. `mise run test:e2e:canary` — must pass (Vogon agent)\\n3. `mise run test:e2e --agent cursor-cli TestDirtyWorkingTree` — the actual failing test\\n\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"41179dd5-b427-4c93-bd53-1656d24a8407\",\"isSid